# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LOCAL MODE CONFIGURATION
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# LOCAL MODE allows the entire Nomads system to run on your local machine
# using ONLY qwen3.5:2b (530MB), eliminating the need for remote infrastructure.
#
# This is ideal for:
# - Testing tools and integrations
# - Development without network dependency
# - Learning the system behavior
# - Running on machines with limited VRAM (16GB+)
#
# Trade-off: Quality is reduced (2b instead of 9b/120b models),
# so outputs are faster but less sophisticated.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ENABLE LOCAL MODE
# Options: "local" | "remote"
# local = Use localhost:11434 (Ollama on this machine)
# remote = Use 100.74.135.83:11434 (Tailscale remote server)
VITE_INFRASTRUCTURE_MODE=local

# LOCAL OLLAMA ENDPOINT (if not running on default port)
# Default: http://localhost:11434
VITE_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434

# OPTIONAL: Local Wayfarer (web scraping) endpoint
# Only needed if running Wayfarer locally (auto-enabled in local mode)
# Default: http://localhost:8889 (Python-based Wayfarer server)
# VITE_WAYFARER_URL=http://localhost:8889

# OPTIONAL: Local SearXNG (meta-search) endpoint
# Only needed if running SearXNG locally (auto-enabled in local mode)
# Default: http://localhost:8888 (Docker-based SearXNG via nginx)
# VITE_SEARXNG_URL=http://localhost:8888

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# USAGE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Make sure Ollama is running:
#    $ ollama serve
#
# 2. Pull qwen3.5:2b (one-time):
#    $ ollama pull qwen3.5:2b
#
# 3. Start dev server:
#    $ npm run dev
#
# 4. The system will automatically use qwen3.5:2b for ALL stages:
#    - Chat/conversation
#    - Research orchestration
#    - Tool calling
#    - Vision/screenshots
#    - Everything else
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ARCHITECTURE IN LOCAL MODE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Before (Production with Remote):
#   - Ollama (remote): qwen3.5:2b/4b/9b/27b + nemotron:120b
#   - Wayfarer (remote): Text scraping + page compression
#   - SearXNG (remote): Meta-search engine
#   - Research: 30+ API calls, high quality output
#   - Creative: Uses nemotron:120b for ads
#
# After (Local Mode):
#   - Ollama (localhost): ONLY qwen3.5:2b
#   - Wayfarer: Optional (can disable research)
#   - SearXNG: Optional (can use built-in search)
#   - Research: Simplified, fewer API calls
#   - Creative: Uses qwen3.5:2b (faster, lower quality)
#   - VRAM: 2-4GB needed (vs 40GB+ for production)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# With qwen3.5:2b for everything:
# ✓ Inference speed: 2-3x faster than 9b
# ✓ VRAM usage: ~3GB (vs 40GB for production)
# ✓ Tool testing: Fully works (image upload, file read, etc)
# ✓ Chat: Works well, quick responses
# ✗ Creative output: Lower quality (no style/personality)
# ✗ Deep reasoning: Simpler logic (no complex planning)
# ✗ Vision analysis: Less detailed (good enough for testing)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
